The paper deals with the problem of testing multilevel planarity, which is a generalization of upward planarity and level planarity. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The paper also presents linear-time algorithms for testing multilevel planarity of embedded graphs with a single source and of oriented cycles, which indicates that it may also belong to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper involves the study of graphs and their properties, which suggests that it may also belong to the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. The paper also presents results on the complexity of the multilevel-planarity testing problem, which suggests that it may belong to the graph theory (cs.GT) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with algorithmic results, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.DL) sub-category.
